{"build_type":"executable","description":"Concise->full transpiler (the single editor/materializer; replace-package-body-from-concise was folded into this per DRY). Request (argv[1]): {\"expand-concise-form-into-package\":{\"path\":\"<ipm>\",\"source\":{<concise package>}}}. The NEW concise form is carried whole in `source`; `path` is the write target. Transpiles concise->full via build_all_functions and writes the full .ipm to `path` (create/overwrite), then emits {written:<path>,bytes:<n>} on stdout. No stdin. Bad request (no argv, unparseable, no arg object, no path, no source, or a source that is not concise — missing kind/package/functions) -> clean JSON {error} on stdout, NO file write, no crash. Reuses parse_argument_vector_json_request, locate_named_member_inside_mapping, add_str_field, build_all_functions, json-tree-node, compute_string_length_by_scanning, open_file_for_writing, write_bytes_to_file, close_open_file, create_empty_string_buffer, append_cstring_into_string_buffer. Writes atomically: serialises to <path>.tmp then renames to <path> (syscall 82) so a crash mid-write cannot corrupt the target., add_number_to_object, emit_result_object_onto_standard_output.","module_name":"expand-concise-format-towards-universe-package","package_name":"expand-concise-format-towards-universe-package","function_definitions":{"expand-concise-format-towards-universe-package":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_path","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"path"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"s_source","variable_type":"str","assignment_operation":"string","source_target":"sou